x4freetext: Hifar reactor
Thermal reactor spectrum.
Thermal neutron flux exceeds 1.x10**13 n/cm2/s (details
for individual samples in subentries 2 and 3)
Fast neutron flux less than 4.x10**11 n/cm2/s
The fast neutron fission rate was less than 0.01%
of the thermal fission rate for all samples.
U3O8,purified as follows. Samples were first dissolved
in 6m HCl with a minimum of nitric acid, evaporated to
dryness and redissolved in 6 m HCl. In order to remove
any possible Te contamination, the solution was placed
on a small anion exchange column (dowex Ag1-x8), the
uranium eluted with 2m HCl and the eluant collected
directly into small, long-necked quartz vials. The
samples were slowly evaporated to dryness and the vials
were then sealed under vacuum.
Chemical separation of tellurium from other species.
Mass-separation by a solid source mass spectrometer
with Re-filament (thermal ionization technique).
by J.R. de Laeter, letter of 9 jan. 1984

(mg)    (n/cm2/s)       (days)
The irradiation time was 28 days for all samples
Uncorrected individual results for 3 samples, yields
are given relative to that of Te-130.
Since Sn-126 has a half-life of about 1.E5 years
its decay can be neglected. Therefore the
measured yield of Te-126 is practically the
sum of independent yields of Sb-126 and Te-126.
Data taken from Table 2 of first reference
The data are not corrected for mass discrimination and
decay.

x4freetext: Yields relative to Te-130.
Weighted average of corrected data
the statistical error is taken from Table 2 of the
first reference, all other data from Table 3.
A mass discrimination of 0.625% per mass unit
was used to correct the data given in subentry 2, based
on a value of 0.68% per mass unit determined
earlier for cadmium isotopes (see Rosman and de Laeter,
Int.J.Mass Spectrom.Ion Phys. 16(1975)385).
The Te-125 data were corrected for radioactive trans-
formations in the mass 125 decay chain. No details are
given.Only a half-life of 2.7 years for Sb-125 is given
in the text.
The statistical error of the weighted average
of the raw data,except for Te-125 where no
weighted average was taken, given as 2 sigma
(see compiler`s note below)
The total error,given as 2 sigma. It includes
the uncertainty in the estimated correction
factor for mass discrimination.
For Te-125 the uncertainty of the corrections
for the decay of precursors is also included,
but no details are given.
Compiler`s note - The assumed 2 sigma nature of the
statistical error was confirmed by the author.
